{"questionId":"19276","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The curve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> has a gradient function given by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mtext>d</mtext><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>d</mtext><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The curve passes through the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Sketch the graph of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;on the same set of axes as part (a)(i).</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/71ba1f79f631f99d3846daba5a993e9125554a0e.png\"></p>\n<p>concave up curve with minimum at approximately&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>asymptote of curve is isocline&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Only award <em><strong>FT</strong></em> from (b) if the above conditions are satisfied.</p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19276","referenceCode":"20N.3.AHL.TZ0.Hca_3c.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Sketch the graph of y=fx on the same set of axes as part (a)(i).","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLa